1. To optimize the extrusion temperature to stabilize extrusion of the resin, homogenize the resin, additives, and particles in the film to reduce unevenness in thickness of the film, and eliminate unevenness in a laminate to improve lamination strength, even if a recycled resin obtained by recycling PET bottles which contain 0.5 mol % or more and 5 mol % or less of isophthalic acid, has high melt viscosity, has been subjected to solid-phase polymerization, and is often mixed with a high crystallization nucleating agent is used;
